  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some ways to put underline and Bold text in Facebook Chat? As previously we can do this by putting text in between underscore(_) and asterisk(*) for underline and bold text respectively?",
  "response": "To style text in Facebook Chat, you can use specific characters to create bold, italic, and strikethrough text. Here are the methods you can use:\n\n1. **Bold Text**:\n   To make text bold, you can enclose the text between two asterisks (`*`) or two underscores (`_`). For example:\n   - `*This text is bold*`\n   - `_This text is also bold_`\n\n2. *Italic Text*:\n   To italicize text, you can enclose the text between single asterisks (`*`) or single underscores (`_`). For example:\n   - `*This text is italic*`\n   - `_This text is also italic_`\n\n3. ~~Strikethrough Text~~:\n   To create strikethrough text, you can enclose the text between two tildes (`~`). For example:\n   - `~This text is strikethrough~`\n\nIt's worth noting that underlining text is not supported in Facebook Chat. If you need to emphasize text, you can use bold or italic formatting instead.\n\nKeep in mind that these formatting options are available in Facebook Messenger and may not work in all platforms or browsers.",
